# EVOKORE-MCP CODEOWNERS
#
# Each line is a path pattern followed by one or more owners.
# The LAST matching pattern wins for any given file.
#
# We deliberately do NOT use `* @mattmre` as a catch-all. A bare wildcard
# pattern can mask intent, makes review noise harder to tune per-area, and
# obscures the fact that some directories vendor upstream code that is not
# truly "owned" by this repo's maintainer.
#
# Reference: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# --- Runtime source ---
/src/                              @mattmre
/scripts/                          @mattmre
/scripts/hooks/                    @mattmre
/plugins/                          @mattmre

# --- Configuration and policy ---
/mcp.config.json                   @mattmre
/damage-control-rules.yaml         @mattmre
/permissions.yml                   @mattmre
/voices.json                       @mattmre
/tsconfig.json                     @mattmre
/vitest.config.ts                  @mattmre
/typedoc.json                      @mattmre
/package.json                      @mattmre
/package-lock.json                 @mattmre
/commitlint.config.js              @mattmre

# --- Skills (curated by the maintainer; vendored upstreams pinned by SHA) ---
